We first need to find $g(5)$ and $f(5)$.  From the definition of $g(x)$, we have $g(5) = 5+3 =8$.  From the definition of $f(x)$, we have $f(5) = 5^{2}-2(5)+5 = 25-10+5 = 20$.  Hence, $f(g(5)) -g(f(5)) = f(8)-g(20)$. From the definition of $f(x)$ and $g(x)$, we know $f(x) = x^{2}-2(5)+5 = x^2 - 10 + 5 = x^2 - 5$ and $g(x) = x+3$ so  \begin{align*}
f(8)-g(20) &= 8^2-5-3-20\\
&= 64+2-23=\boxed{43}.
\end{align*}

Let the positive integer be $x$. We translate the given information into an equation: $(3x)^2-x=2010$. Expanding $(3x)^2-x$ gives $9x^2-x=2010$. Re-arranging the equation and excluding the extraneous root $x=-\frac{2230}{3}$, we get
\[2010+x=9x^2\]
\[9x^2-x-2010=0.\] Factoring the quadratic gives $(3x + 63)(3x - 32)=0$, and we obtain $x = \boxed{32}$.

