We distribute to obtain \begin{align*}
x(3x^2-2)-5(x^2-2x+7) &= 3x^3-2x - 5x^2 +10x -35\\
&=\boxed{3x^3 -5x^2 +8x -35}.
\end{align*}

We set up a system of equations.  Since we are told that "The sum of two numbers is $30$," we get: \begin{align*}
x + y &= 30.
\end{align*}We also know that "If we double the larger number, and subtract three times the smaller number, the result is $5$," which we can translate to:\begin{align*}
2x - 3y &= 5.
\end{align*}We could solve this system by substitution.  From $x + y = 30,$ we have $y = 30 - x.$  Substituting $y = 30 - x$ into the second equation, we get $2x - 3(30 - x) = 5,$ which gives us $x = 23.$  Then $y = 30 - 23 = 7,$ so the positive difference between the two numbers is $23 - 7 = \boxed{16}.$

We distribute and combine like terms: \begin{align*}
3(x^2 - x^3+x) +3(x +2x^3- 3x^2 + 3x^5+x^3) -5(1+x-4x^3 - x^2) &= 3x^2 - 3x^3+3x + 3x +6x^3- 9x^2 + 9x^5+3x^3 -5-5x+20x^3 + 5x^2\\ &= 9x^5+24x^3 - 8x^2 +4x -5.
\end{align*} Thus, the coefficient of $x^3$ is $\boxed{24}$.

The midpoint of $\overline{AB}$ is $\left(\frac{24 + 3}{2}, \frac{7 + 4}{2}\right) = \left(\frac{27}{2}, \frac{11}{2}\right),$ so the slope of $\overleftrightarrow{AB}$ is
\[\frac{11/2 - 4}{27/2 - 3} = \frac{3}{2}.\]Therefore, the slope of the line $p$ is $-\frac{2}{3}.$  It follows that the line $p$ passes through $\left(\frac{27}{2}, \frac{11}{2}\right),$ so its equation is
\[y - \frac{11}{2} = -\frac{2}{3} \left( x - \frac{27}{2} \right),\]or $2x - 3y = 22.$

Substituting into this equation $2x - 3y = 22$ into $y = \frac{2x + 26}{3}$ (Notice that $x$ is on the left side of $y$ in the fraction), we get
\[2x - 3 \cdot \frac{2x + 26}{3} = 22.\]Solving, we find $x = 14.$  Then $y = \frac{2(14) + 26}{3} = \frac{46}{3},$ so $2x - 4y = \boxed{-\frac{8}{3}}.$

