First, looking at the expression we can combine like terms: \begin{align*}
2x+8x^2+9-(4-2x-8x^2) &= 2x + 8x^2 + 9 - 4 + 2x + 8x^2 \\
&= (2x+2x)+(8x^2+8x^2)+(9-4) \\
&= \boxed{16x^2 + 4x + 5}.
\end{align*}

Completing the square, we get \[(x^2+12x)+(y^2+16y)=0.\]We "complete the square" in the $x$ terms by adding $(12/2)^2=36$ to both sides, and "complete the square" in the $y$ terms by adding $(16/2)^2=64$ to both sides.  This gives us \begin{align*}
(x^2+12x+36)+(y^2+16y+64)&=100 \\
(x+6)^2+(y+8)^2&=100.
\end{align*}Thus, the equation describes a circle in the $xy$-plane with radius $\sqrt{100}=10.$  The area of this circle is $\pi (10)^2=\boxed{100\pi}.$

